node.text:
When HEALING calls…and it tastes like warm malasadas and tropical Mai tai’s, feels like ziplining hundreds of yards over a valley of sweet pineapples, and smells like fresh ocean water lapping the shores of a private beach….you answer the call. Even though it might force you to hike a mile high crater with the sun beating down on your face, it also promises to give you the most majestic view you’ve ever seen, once you arrive. You may have to work a bit for it, but it’s worth it. THIS is what Hawaii did for me, and I will forever be grateful for it. 

If you look at the picture from my previous post, you’d see a worn down human being with nothing left to give. And even though it’s going to take a summer of restoration, I can say that I’m coming back home with a lot more in my tank than I had when I left. 

Mahalo Hawaii for sharing your land, your food, your culture with the world. You left an impression on my soul. ❤️ Teacher peeps, I hope this is a summer of Healing for each one of you, too. Cheers, friends…we made it 👊🏼 #summerbreak #hawaii #teachers #tiredteacher #remoteteaching #hybridteaching

node.text:
✅ Classroom packed 
📁 Files updated 
😵‍💫 Teacher cooked 

You won’t find a cute selfie of me in a packed-up classroom…this is the best I got for a school year that nearly did me in. It feels like the weight of a million expectations is slowly being lifted off my back and honestly, it’s going to take some time to release it. My SOUL is 15-months-exhausted and right now, relief looks a lot more like weeping than celebrating, but it is what it is.

Check my “we made it” highlights (temporarily) for the real, raw feels…😭 Congrats to those who are done! And to those of you who are fighting your way to the finish line, we are all pulling for you.💪🏼 If you need me, I’ll be on the couch, eating Crumbl cookies, taking naps at will, and giving myself the break I so desperately need. Teachers friends, I love and respect each one of you.❤️

#tiredteacher #teacherproblems #remoteteaching #distanceteaching #remotelearning2020 #pandemicteaching #hybridteaching #hyflexteaching #tired

node.text:
That one friend, who took their hate for the drab shields and turned it into something fab. 😂 I should preface by saying that I’m a massive perfectionist and my need for order is extremely high. So if this setup gives you hives, I completely understand it! 👯‍♀️ HOWEVER, none of this hot mess actually bothers me. 🤷🏻‍♀️

This school year, I found myself needing all of the things (big or small) that bring me joy: coffee, cheezits, chocolate, and new packs of flair pens. So I say, “Rainbow-pen-and-origami it up, little friend...find your joy!” And I’m going to leave this picture here on my feed to remind me to find beauty in the chaos. Plus, this just might be the desk of a future teacher...🌈🖍🍎 Now how about you...does this desk drive you crazy? 😨🤣 #pandemicteaching #hybridteaching #teacherproblems #distanceteaching #remotelearning

node.text:
I got 99 problems, but keeping my desks lined up ain’t one of them! ✅😂 I hate the *required* rows and columns of desks in my room right now, but these rainbow carpet spots (Velcro!) are giving me all kinds of life!! 🌈🙌🏼🙌🏼 

I now dismiss my kids by colors (“Red row, line up for lunch...”), and all they need to do at the end of the day is line up the front of their desks with the center of the dot (because the ever-drifting desks are killing me!) 🤦🏻‍♀️😂 

Is it all kinds of “extra”...? YEP. Am I sorry? NOPE. 🤷🏻‍♀️ In fact, it’s almost like being reunited with my old rainbow rug again (RIP Rainbow Rug 💀🌈😭❤️) Find the carpet spots in my profile link (check the Amazon links) #teacherproblems #rainbow #colorcoding #typeAteacher #typeA #itsfine #hybridteaching

node.text:
NO BUDGET TASK CARDS ✅: when you need an engaging activity but don’t have the time or energy to design something cute and then obsess about laminating it. This is pretty much how I roll these days...high engagement, low/no prep (aka - flying by the seat of my pants) because hyflex teaching is hard. 🤷🏻‍♀️😬 

I made these cards during recess, when I noticed the kids were tired (and so was I!) And guess what...it worked! The kids were *equally* as engaged with these no-budget task cards as they are with my cute, colorful, laminated ones. 🙌🏼🙌🏼

If there’s one thing I’ve learned this year, it’s how to LET GO. My stuff doesn’t have to be cute to be engaging and fun. So...my tired teacher friends, if you need something quick and easy...grab a Sharpie, a few notecards, and then write out some review problems. Tape the cards around the room and have the kids record answers on a plain sheet of paper. They’ll think you’re the best teacher ever. 🤩 Done and done! #hyflexteacher #hybridteaching #teacher #tiredteacher #taskcards #teacherproblems

node.text:
Tomorrow is our third First Day of School. 🤯 First, we were 100% remote; then hyflex half-day. Now, we’ll be hyflex full-day. I *kind of* prepared my room and I *almost* have a plan for tomorrow...but it’s fine, everything is fine. 😅

If you’ve watched my stories, you know it’s impossible for me to encapsulate all of my feels in one Instagram post. So I’ll just say this: I can’t wait to see my kids tomorrow, and bring back the magic and synergy of the classroom. ✨ I can’t wait to get my groove back, and maybe be able to plan more than *one* day in advance.🗓 And at the same time, I also can’t wait for summer. 🤷🏻‍♀️😎 Reality is: I am DIGGING DEEP to see this year through. 

Teacher friends, you have worked, planned, prepped, posted, reposted, copied, pasted, linked, relinked 🔗, graded, monitored, redirected, muted, unmuted, screen-shared, assessed, reassessed, Google’d, Canvas’d, Schoology’d, Microsoft’d, and have basically pulled off the impossible all year long. We have done ALL the things, for ALL the people. We have been everything, to everyone. And we are EXHAUSTED beyond our bandwidth. But the end is in sight. It feels far away, but I swear it’s there. 🙏🏼

So if your second, or third, or fourth First Day of School is just around the corner, embrace it as best as you *humanly* can. And somehow, LET’S DO THIS!!! 💪🏼😩 This concludes my SEMI-INSPIRATIONAL post of the day 😂 #survival #hybridteaching #teacherproblems #remotelearning #distancelearning #sendcoffee #godhelpme

node.text:
Pretty browser 🖥😍...and I PROMISE this will be the LAST post about tab groups...🤗 But I had to show you guys: these are grouped tabs with a *DARK* color scheme, because I too, like to live dangerously...😂 

Personally, I am sick of looking at any kind of computer screen, but making it pretty really does help! And this small fix just might appeal to my type A friends who saw my previous post about tab groups, and didn’t love the colors, or the fact that the orange tabs have a black font, while all the others are white. If ya know, ya know...🤷🏻‍♀️

To accomplish this look, go to the bottom right corner of your Google Chrome and select “customize.” You can choose a brand new color scheme (which changes the tab colors) and you can even download themes from the Chrome store to put images and designs on your chrome browser. 🎨 Now go prettify those browsers! 💻 #distanceteaching #remoteteaching #hybridlearning #googlechrome #google @google #edtechteachers #edtechchat #pdwithapl #googleET #teacherproblems

node.text:
TAB GROUP IDEAS💡Now that we’re all happily grouping our Chrome tabs (aren’t we?!)...here are some different ideas for how you can group yours, so people will stop judging you for your hot mess internet tabs 🙈😂 (Pinch and zoom in to take a closer look)

You can create groups for days, priority/importance, class number, topics, or my favorite: just use emoji without words 🙌🏼🙌🏼 Drop a comment and let us know how you like to keep tabs on your tabs ✅

If you need to know how to do this, watch my latest Reel or my “Tab Tips” highlight for a full tutorial. **SIDE NOTE: The groups will save if you have your chrome settings at “pick up where I left off” on startup, unless your district has blocked that feature 😩 This works on Macs AND PC’s (I use it on both)** #googlechrome @google #googleET #distanceteaching #hybridlearning #remoteteaching #organization #teachertechtip #edtechteachers #edtech

Organize your 27+ tabs, using “tab groups” in Google Chrome 🗂💻 Drag tabs into any groups you create: days of the week, section #’s, subjects, to-do’s/priorities, or anything you choose! 

I wouldn’t recommend keeping tons of tabs open, as it will slow your computer down a bit, but tab groups are a great way to keep everything tidy. They will also save when you close and reopen Chrome. 

See the full tutorial in my “Tab Tips” highlight. Tag a buddy who’s might need to keep better tabs on their tabs...👯‍♀️ #edtech #googlechrome #teachertechtips #distanceteaching #remoteteaching #googleET #googleclassroom #google #pdwithapl @google
